<subSubSection pageId="40" pageNumber="2822" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="40.[826,1468,1180,1955]" pageId="40" pageNumber="2822">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Zheng &amp; Wittouck &amp; Salvetti &amp; Franz &amp; Harris &amp; Mattarelli &amp; O’Toole &amp; Pot &amp; Vandamme &amp; Walter &amp; Watanabe &amp; Wuyts &amp; Felis &amp; Gänzle &amp; Lebeer" authorityYear="2020" box="[828,1110,1260,1284]" class="Bacilli" family="Lactobacillaceae" genus="Ligilactobacillus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Bacteria" order="Lactobacillales" pageId="40" pageNumber="2822" phylum="Firmicutes" rank="species" species="araffinosus">
<emphasis box="[828,1110,1260,1284]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="2822">Ligilactobacillus araffinosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(a.raf.fi.no’sus. Gr. pref. 
<emphasis box="[1357,1370,1261,1284]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="2822">a</emphasis>
not; N.L. masc. adj. 
<emphasis box="[940,1041,1291,1315]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="2822">raffinosus</emphasis>
of raffinose; N.L. masc. adj. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Zheng &amp; Wittouck &amp; Salvetti &amp; Franz &amp; Harris &amp; Mattarelli &amp; O’Toole &amp; Pot &amp; Vandamme &amp; Walter &amp; Watanabe &amp; Wuyts &amp; Felis &amp; Gänzle &amp; Lebeer" authorityYear="2020" box="[1346,1460,1291,1315]" class="Bacilli" family="Lactobacillaceae" genus="Ligilactobacillus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Bacteria" order="Lactobacillales" pageId="40" pageNumber="2822" phylum="Firmicutes" rank="species" species="araffinosus">
<emphasis box="[1346,1460,1291,1315]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="2822">araffinosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, not fermenting raffinose).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="41" lastPageNumber="2823" pageId="40" pageNumber="2822" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="40.[826,1468,1180,1955]" pageId="40" pageNumber="2822">
Basonym: 
<taxonomicName authority="Fujisawa et al. 1985" authorityName="Fujisawa" authorityYear="1985" class="Bacilli" family="Lactobacillaceae" genus="Lactobacillus" kingdom="Bacteria" order="Lactobacillales" pageId="40" pageNumber="2822" phylum="Firmicutes" rank="subSpecies" species="aviarius" subSpecies="araffinosus">
<emphasis box="[941,1170,1369,1393]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="2822">Lactobacillus aviarius</emphasis>
subsp. 
<emphasis box="[1252,1366,1369,1393]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="2822">araffinosus</emphasis>
Fujisawa 
<emphasis box="[828,871,1400,1424]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="2822">et al</emphasis>
. 1985
</taxonomicName>
, 223 
<superScript attach="right" box="[985,1005,1399,1413]" fontSize="6" pageId="40" pageNumber="2822">VP</superScript>
; Fujisawa 
<emphasis box="[1114,1158,1400,1424]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="2822">et al</emphasis>
. 1986, (Effective publication: Fujisawa 
<emphasis box="[926,970,1431,1455]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="2822">et al</emphasis>
., 1984, 419).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="40.[826,1468,1180,1955]" pageId="40" pageNumber="2822">
Placement of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Zheng &amp; Wittouck &amp; Salvetti &amp; Franz &amp; Harris &amp; Mattarelli &amp; O’Toole &amp; Pot &amp; Vandamme &amp; Walter &amp; Watanabe &amp; Wuyts &amp; Felis &amp; Gänzle &amp; Lebeer" authorityYear="2020" box="[971,1112,1478,1502]" class="Bacilli" family="Lactobacillaceae" genus="Ligilactobacillus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Bacteria" order="Lactobacillales" pageId="40" pageNumber="2822" phylum="Firmicutes" rank="species" species="araffinosus">
<emphasis box="[971,1112,1478,1502]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="2822">L. araffinosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in a separate species is supported by ANI values and digital DNA–DNA hybridization [
<bibRefCitation author="Wittouck S &amp; Wuyts S &amp; Meehan CJ &amp; van Noort V &amp; Lebeer S." box="[1380,1411,1509,1533]" pageId="40" pageNumber="2822" refId="ref60115" refString="10. Wittouck S, Wuyts S, Meehan CJ, van Noort V, Lebeer S. A genome-based species taxonomy of the Lactobacillus Genus Complex. mSystems 2019; 4: e 00264 - 19." type="journal volume" year="2019">10</bibRefCitation>
]. The availability of the genome sequences of the 
<typeStatus box="[1308,1355,1541,1565]" pageId="40" pageNumber="2822">type</typeStatus>
strains of both subspecies revealed that they are only distantly related with an ANI value of 88.98%, substantially below the 95–96 % threshold recognised for the species level. Furthermore, their core nucleotide identity (CNI) [
<bibRefCitation author="Wittouck S &amp; Wuyts S &amp; Meehan CJ &amp; van Noort V &amp; Lebeer S." box="[1243,1273,1666,1690]" pageId="40" pageNumber="2822" refId="ref60115" refString="10. Wittouck S, Wuyts S, Meehan CJ, van Noort V, Lebeer S. A genome-based species taxonomy of the Lactobacillus Genus Complex. mSystems 2019; 4: e 00264 - 19." type="journal volume" year="2019">10</bibRefCitation>
] is 91.1, which is below the 94 % threshold at which two strains are allocated to the same species. Finally, their 
<emphasis box="[1175,1253,1728,1752]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="2822">in silico</emphasis>
DDH value is 37.80, which additionally supports that these two subspecies should be recognised as different species [
<bibRefCitation author="Wittouck S &amp; Wuyts S &amp; Meehan CJ &amp; van Noort V &amp; Lebeer S." box="[1192,1223,1791,1815]" pageId="40" pageNumber="2822" refId="ref60115" refString="10. Wittouck S, Wuyts S, Meehan CJ, van Noort V, Lebeer S. A genome-based species taxonomy of the Lactobacillus Genus Complex. mSystems 2019; 4: e 00264 - 19." type="journal volume" year="2019">10</bibRefCitation>
].
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="40.[826,1468,1180,1955]" lastBlockId="41.[121,760,182,452]" lastPageId="41" lastPageNumber="2823" pageId="40" pageNumber="2822">
Cells are Gram- positive, non-motile, non-spore-forming rods with rounded ends, usually occurring singly or in short chains. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Zheng &amp; Wittouck &amp; Salvetti &amp; Franz &amp; Harris &amp; Mattarelli &amp; O’Toole &amp; Pot &amp; Vandamme &amp; Walter &amp; Watanabe &amp; Wuyts &amp; Felis &amp; Gänzle &amp; Lebeer" authorityYear="2020" box="[906,1044,1900,1924]" class="Bacilli" family="Lactobacillaceae" genus="Ligilactobacillus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Bacteria" order="Lactobacillales" pageId="40" pageNumber="2822" phylum="Firmicutes" rank="species" species="araffinosus">
<emphasis box="[906,1044,1900,1924]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="2822">L. araffinosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
strains ferment trehalose and cellobiose, they do not produce acid from galactose, lactose, melibiose and raffinose [
<bibRefCitation author="Fujisawa T &amp; Shirasaka S &amp; Watabe J &amp; Mitsuoka T." box="[273,304,182,206]" pageId="41" pageNumber="2823" pagination="414 - 420" refId="ref61679" refString="51. Fujisawa T, Shirasaka S, Watabe J, Mitsuoka T. Lactobacillus aviarius sp. nov.: a new species isolated from the intestine of chickens. Syst Appl Microbiol 1984; 5: 414 - 420." type="journal article" year="1984">51</bibRefCitation>
]. The genome size of the 
<typeStatus box="[572,618,183,207]" pageId="41" pageNumber="2823">type</typeStatus>
strain is 1.48 Mbp. The mol% G+C content of DNA is 38.1.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="41.[121,760,182,452]" box="[121,610,259,283]" pageId="41" pageNumber="2823">Isolated from the intestine and faeces of birds.</paragraph>
